SIMPLE: graduator
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Graduator
<hw>Grad"u*a"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who determines or indicates graduation; <as>as, a graduator of
instruments</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instrument for dividing any line, right or curve,
into small, regular intervals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An apparatus for diffusing a solution, as brine or
vinegar, over a large surface, for exposure to the air.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gradus</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
